      "content": "Those feelings are valid, as regulations are often viewed through the lens of immediate burdens rather than abstract environmental goals. While the intent is genuine climate protection, the effectiveness depends on whether smaller firms can implement these changes without being priced out of the market or displaced by larger competitors. Many experts argue that without adjusting regulatory structures to account for economies of scale, these measures may succeed globally while inadvertently harming local small business survival.",
